# General Rules

## Git permissions

NEVER run `git commit`, `git push`, `git rebase`, `git reset --hard`, `git merge`, or any other write/destructive git command unless the user **explicitly** requests it in the current message.

Read-only git commands are allowed freely: `git status`, `git log`, `git diff`, `git show`, `git branch`.

## Code changes

- Always read a file before editing it
- Do not add comments that only describe what the code does — comments should explain non-obvious intent or trade-offs
- Fix linter errors you introduce; do not fix pre-existing ones unless asked
